The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
		 Monday, April 19, 2004  Q amp;A				 Upbringing cost
																																																																																													Can I get tax exemption on education loan taken for my sons higher studies? 																																																																													A. K. Sharma, Bokaro
																																																																																													Up to a maximum of Rs 40,000 per annum, which includes both the principal and interest, for a period of 8 years, is allowed as deduction under section 80E for repayment of education loan. 																																					Gifts galore																																																																																															Would a gift received from a father considered as income for the son in that financial year? How is it possible to establish the income as a gift? 																																																																																															Is the income of Rs 1,50,000 on which a rebate of 20 per cent is allowed, arrived at after deductions under section 80? 																																																																													M. . Acharya, Calcutta
																																																																																													If the gift is in the form of cash, then no tax needs to be paid. If the gift is an immovable property, then a stamp duty based on the value of the property has to be paid. To establish the receipt as a gift, a deed has to be worked out on stamp paper of due denomination. 																																																																																													Deductions under section 80 are not considered while arriving at the income of Rs 1,50,000 on which tax rebate of 20 per cent is allowed. 																																					PPF poser																																																																																															 maturity, I have reinvested my PPF deposit for a further period of five years. Can I withdraw the full or part amount of my deposit?																																																																													D. K. Saha, Calcutta
																																																																																													You can withdraw either the full or part amount of the money and will receive interest for the duration you kept your money invested in the fund.																																					Share gains																																																																																															What is the difference between short-term capital gains earned from selling the shares and gains acquired from trading of shares? 																																																																													R. K. Singhal, Durgapur
																																																																																													Trading means either buying or selling of shares. Any profit or gain from the sale of shares held for 12 months or less will be considered as short-term capital gains and is included in the annual income. 												If you have any queries about investing or taxes or a high-cost purchase you are planning, mail to: btgraphabpmail.com, or write to: Business Telegraph, 6 Prafulla Sarkar Street, Calcutta 700 001
